    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM: A. H. BELMONT",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: UNKNOWN OBJECT OVER OAK RIDGE, TENNESSEE, MARCH 1, 1950;",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "[REDACTED], COMPLAINANT; VITAL FACILITIES; INTERNAL",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "SECURITY",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "Reference is made to my memorandum of March 3, 1950, reflecting",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "a call from SAC Robey, of Knoxville, in the above-entitled matter.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "On the morning of March 6, 1950, I called SAC Robey to ascertain what he",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "had found out concerning this matter. He advised that a teletype had been sent",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "reflecting that there was some question of [REDACTED] reliability and knowledge on",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "radar theory; that CIC and OSI are continuing their interest in the matter; and that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "the CIA technician from Washington had not arrived.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "SAC Robey will report any further developments.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
